pageContext.claim: “You know, they said they [Democrats] picked up the House in '18, but I didn't run in '18. You know, big difference when you run, '16 I ran in '18 I didn't run, and they did. They picked up -- they picked up some seats.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump was not on the ballot, but he traversed the country and held dozens of rallies for congressional candidates. Still, Republicans lost control of the House.
